Gateway Actions for OPNsense

Runs configurable actions (e.g. restart all WireGuard tunnels) when a gateway
changes state. Built for multi-WAN failover setups where box-originated tunnels
must re-establish over the new uplink after a failover or failback.

Provides a Services GUI with a live status dashboard (gateway states, WireGuard
handshakes, event history), a rule editor and a master enable switch. Rules match
on watched gateways and a trigger (any / down / up), run a chosen action, and are
rate-limited by a per-rule cooldown to avoid restart storms on a flapping line.

WWW: https://github.com/synapticmeta/os-gwactions
